sql:
SELECT MAX(total_amount)
FROM invoices
WHERE vendor_id = 100;

SELECT i.*, p.*
FROM invoices i
LEFT JOIN payments p ON i.invoice_id = p.invoice_id;

external_knowledge:
- "fertile soil sprouting more than three invoices" is a metaphor for vendors who have issued more than three invoices;
- "bustling activity in this period" refers to the high volume of invoices indicating active business engagement;
- "within the last month" refers to the condition of invoices being issued in the past 30 days.

- "a handful of bills" refers to more than 5 invoices;
- "largest payment exceeding a thousand dollars" means the maximum amount of a line item in a paid invoice is greater than 1000;
- "average invoice amount" is calculated as the total paid amount divided by the total number of invoices for each vendor, rounded up to the nearest integer.
